   Actually, IBM's plan is to concentrate on the microkernel architecture
version of OS/2 based on their Mach 3.0 implementation.  Porting to the
PC involves only a port of the microkernel.  This is, of course the 
reason why NT is so portable.
   Why not advise people of a better way.  I rememeber the days(1989) when
it was like pulling teeth to get my supervisors to downsize from
a predominantly mainframe environment to a 386/486 PC network.  
Everybody was using mainframes who did our sort of work, but later
it was clear that downsizing was indeed the right thing to do and we were
lucky we did it sooner rather than later.


